# Cursor Rules for Backend

## Formatting
- Use Prettier for all TypeScript, JavaScript, and JSON files
- Format on save should be enabled
- Use single quotes for strings
- Use semicolons
- Use trailing commas
- Tab width: 2 spaces

## Code Style
- Follow TypeScript best practices
- Use proper type annotations
- Avoid `any` types when possible
- Use descriptive variable and function names
- Keep functions small and focused

## File Organization
- Keep models in `src/models/`
- Keep services in `src/services/`
- Keep routes in `src/routes/`
- Keep utilities in `src/utils/`
- Use consistent file naming: `feature.type.ts` 